comments: She is very nice, but not very helpful when the course is online. She takes points off for every little thing, and it\'s only a one credit course. Easy A assignments I\'ve gotten at least two points taken off so things such as wrong text color or not doing what she wanted the exact way she expected it.

Mrs. Cobb was in the bottom two for professors I had at BW. She taught us as though we were second graders. She was also very demeaning to students, myself in particular, for expressing confusion in regards to her instructions. I would not recommend her to anyone.
I was looking forward to taking this course. It was very useful in my field experience. The professor knows how to use technology in the classroom. I hope to take a course with Dr. Cobb again.
Best class for learning how to use technology in the classroom.
A nice lady but she does not really teach anything at all. The class consists of busy work with no application to the classroom. She is really lenient with due dates which helps.
Dr. Cobb is very knowledgeable. Awesome professor, wonderful class.
Great Class! Now I know how to use technology in the classroom.
This is a great class. We are learning how to use technology with all types of learners. I love the free software.
This is one of my favorite classes at B-W. I recommend that you take Dr. Cobb\'s class you will learn a lot about how to use tech. in the classroom.
Dr. Cobb has a positive attitude and she is always willing and able to answer our questions.
Very sweet woman but hard ot understand. Assignments not clearly explained. Does not answer quesitons with the correct response.
Dr. Cobb is very knowledgeable in technology and it\'s use in the classroom. This is one of the best courses that I have ever taken.
I really enjoyed this course. I learned a lot form Dr. Cobb. She was was easy to talk to and she was always available to help us. Great Professor.

She\'s a very nice woman, but this class was made much harder than necessary, due to her lack of clarity. This was an educational technology class and I felt as though she often did not know anything beyond what the textbook said. If you ask a question, she will answer it by poorly rephrasing the oricinally unclear assignment.
